Although in this case it is correct, I am thinking about a more general approach of defining the ingress via values.yaml (which allows override). Similar to common.resources template maybe.
Example where this approach won't work is AAI (there are many paths):
# aai
      - backend:
          serviceName: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.name }}
          servicePort: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.port }}
        path: /aai
      - backend:
          serviceName: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.name }}
          servicePort: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.port }}
        path: /services/aai/webapp
      - backend:
          serviceName: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.name }}
          servicePort: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.port }}
        path: /services/routerService
      - backend:
          serviceName: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.name }}
          servicePort: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.port }}
        path: /api/v2/storeAnalytics
      - backend:
          serviceName: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.name }}
          servicePort: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.port }}
        path: /rest/search
      - backend:
          serviceName: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.name }}
          servicePort: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.port }}
        path: /rest/subscription
      - backend:
          serviceName: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.name }}
          servicePort: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.port }}
        path: /rest/visualization
      - backend:
          serviceName: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.name }}
          servicePort: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.port }}
        path: /auditSearchQuery
      - backend:
          serviceName: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.name }}
          servicePort: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.port }}
        path: /visualization
      - backend:
          serviceName: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.name }}
          servicePort: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.port }}
        path: /subscription
      - backend:
          serviceName: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.name }}
          servicePort: {{ .Values.ingress.service.aai.port }}
        path: /favicon.ico

I think the annotations need to come from values.yaml also.
Similar to: 
{{- with .Values.ingress.annotations }}
  annotations:
{{ toYaml . | indent 4 }}
{{- end }}
and in values.yaml there can be:
  annotations:
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/proxy-body-size: "500m"
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/ssl-redirect: "false"
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/secure-backends: "false"
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/configuration-snippet: |
      more_set_headers "EPService: true";
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/server-snippet: |
      underscores_in_headers on;
    ingress.kubernetes.io/ssl-redirect: "false"
    ingress.kubernetes.io/secure-backends: "false"
    ingress.kubernetes.io/configuration-snippet: |
      more_set_headers "EPService: true";
    ingress.kubernetes.io/server-snippet: |
      underscores_in_headers on;
